The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Boy from UK to take part

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: Dishan Barua, son of GM Dibyendu Barua and IWM Saheli, will be making his competitive debut in The Telegraph Schools Chess Championship beginning at the Alekhine Chess Club on Wednesday. 

The 18th edition of the countrys premier school championship is being presented by Linc with Bata being the co-sponsor. 

The meet will see promising players from all across the country, as well as six from Bangladesh and one from England, taking part. 

All eys will be on England resident Ankush Khandelwal, who was champion in the under-14 category of the British championship. He has a rating of 1934. 

Among the top ten rated players, seven are from Bengal. Participants from 11 states ? Bengal, Rajasthan, Tripura, Madhya Pradesh, Delhi, Jharkhand, Orissa, Assam, Manipur, Chattisgarh and Bihar ? will be vying for honours in the 11-round Swiss League format tournament. 

The tournament will see a total of 34 Fide-rated players, with Kh. Sanjoy Singh (2150) of Manipur being the top seed. He is followed by state boy Debaditya Sinha (2133) and Debashish Das (2120) of Orissa. 

A total of 280 students from more than 130 schools have confirmed participation. 

The youngest participant will be Shashvat Kumar, a Prep student of Miranda Hall. 

This is the grand finale after the Guwahati, Bhubaneswar and Jamshedpur legs. The final round is slated for December 29. 

The winner will be richer by Rs 15,000 and a trophy, while the runner-up will get Rs 10000 and a trophy. 

The total prize money of on offer is Rs 60000. There will also be prizes for each of the age-group winners. 

Jain Shrenhik Daklia of Chattisgarh is the defending champion. 




